title: X3D V4.0 JSON Schema, generated 2026/02/19 11:07:04
description: Experimental JSON Schema for X3D V4.0.  License: Web3D Consortium License: https://www.web3d.org/license

-NamedUSEField.title: NamedUSEField
-NamedUSEField.description: A USE field with a @name field

#comment.description: #comment statements are the only allowed in -children node when using a USE field

-USEField.title: USENode
-USEField.description: A USE field without a @name field

#comment.description: #comment statements are the only allowed in -children node when using a USE field

@geoSystem.$comment: Coordinate reference system identifier tokens. Exactly one of three systems: GD/GDC (geographic degrees), UTM (universal transverse mercator), or GC/GCC (geocentric).

@geoSystem-GD.title: geoSystem GD/GDC � Geographic Degrees
@geoSystem-GD.$comment: Geographic lat/lon degrees. Optional second token selects ellipsoid datum; defaults to WE (WGS84 ellipsoid).

@geoSystem-GC.title: geoSystem GC/GCC � Geocentric
@geoSystem-GC.$comment: Earth-centered geocentric coordinate system. No additional parameters.

@geoSystem-ellipsoid.title: geoSystem ellipsoid datum
@geoSystem-ellipsoid.$comment: Reference ellipsoid. WGS84 is the datum name; the 22 two-letter codes are ellipsoid identifiers. Defaults to WE.

@geoSystem-UTM-zone.title: UTM zone number
@geoSystem-UTM-zone.$comment: Zone 1�60 prefixed with Z. Leading zero is optional: Z1 and Z01 are both valid.

AcousticProperties.title: AcousticProperties
AcousticProperties.description: AcousticProperties specifies the interaction of sound waves with characteristics of geometric objects in the scene.

Analyser.title: Analyser
Analyser.description: Analyser provides real-time frequency and time-domain analysis information, without any signal-processing change to the audio stream which is passed unprocessed from input to output.

Anchor.title: Anchor
Anchor.description: Anchor is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

Appearance.title: Appearance
Appearance.description: Appearance specifies the visual properties of geometry by containing the Material, ImageTexture/MovieTexture/PixelTexture, FillProperties, LineProperties, programmable shader nodes (ComposedShader, PackagedShader, ProgramShader) and TextureTransform nodes.

Arc2D.title: Arc2D
Arc2D.description: Arc2D is a line-based geometry node that defines a linear circular arc with center (0,0) in X-Y plane, with angles measured starting at positive x-axis and sweeping towards positive y-axis.

ArcClose2D.title: ArcClose2D
ArcClose2D.description: ArcClose2D is a polygonal geometry node that defines a linear circular arc, closed by PIE or CHORD line segments, with center (0,0) in X-Y plane, with angles measured starting at positive x-axis and sweeping towards positive y-axis.

AudioClip.title: AudioClip
AudioClip.description: AudioClip provides audio data used by parent Sound nodes.

AudioDestination.title: AudioDestination
AudioDestination.description: AudioDestination node represents the final audio destination and is what user ultimately hears, typically from the speakers of user device.

Background.title: Background
Background.description: Background simulates ground and sky, using vertical arrays of wraparound color values.

BallJoint.title: BallJoint
BallJoint.description: BallJoint represents an unconstrained joint between two bodies that pivot about a common anchor point.

Billboard.title: Billboard
Billboard.description: Billboard is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

BiquadFilter.title: BiquadFilter
BiquadFilter.description: BiquadFilter node is an AudioNode processor implementing common low-order filters.

BlendedVolumeStyle.title: BlendedVolumeStyle
BlendedVolumeStyle.description: BlendedVolumeStyle combines rendering of two voxel data sets into one by blending voxel values.

BooleanFilter.title: BooleanFilter
BooleanFilter.description: BooleanFilter selectively passes true, false or negated events.

BooleanSequencer.title: BooleanSequencer
BooleanSequencer.description: BooleanSequencer generates periodic discrete Boolean values.

BooleanToggle.title: BooleanToggle
BooleanToggle.description: BooleanToggle maintains state and negates output when a true input is provided.

BooleanTrigger.title: BooleanTrigger
BooleanTrigger.description: BooleanTrigger converts time events to boolean true events.

BoundaryEnhancementVolumeStyle.title: BoundaryEnhancementVolumeStyle
BoundaryEnhancementVolumeStyle.description: BoundaryEnhancementVolumeStyle provides boundary enhancement for the volume rendering style.

BoundedPhysicsModel.title: BoundedPhysicsModel
BoundedPhysicsModel.description: BoundedPhysicsModel provides user-defined geometrical boundaries for particle motion.

Box.title: Box
Box.description: Box is a geometry node specifying a rectangular cuboid.

BufferAudioSource.title: BufferAudioSource
BufferAudioSource.description: BufferAudioSource node represents a memory-resident audio asset that can contain one or more channels.

CADAssembly.title: CADAssembly
CADAssembly.description: CADAssembly holds a set of Computer-Aided Design (CAD) assemblies or parts grouped together.

CADFace.title: CADFace
CADFace.description: CADFace holds geometry representing one face in a Computer-Aided Design (CAD) CADPart.

CADLayer.title: CADLayer
CADLayer.description: CADLayer nodes define a hierarchy that shows layer structure for a Computer-Aided Design (CAD) model.

CADPart.title: CADPart
CADPart.description: CADPart is an atomic part that defines both coordinate-system location and the faces that constitute a part in a Computer-Aided Design (CAD) model.

CartoonVolumeStyle.title: CartoonVolumeStyle
CartoonVolumeStyle.description: CartoonVolumeStyle generates cartoon-style non-photorealistic rendering of associated volumetric data.

ChannelMerger.title: ChannelMerger
ChannelMerger.description: ChannelMerger unites different input channels into a single output channel.

ChannelSelector.title: ChannelSelector
ChannelSelector.description: ChannelSelector selects a single channel output from all input channels.

ChannelSplitter.title: ChannelSplitter
ChannelSplitter.description: ChannelSplitter separates the different channels of a single audio source into a set of monophonic output channels.

Circle2D.title: Circle2D
Circle2D.description: Circle2D is a geometry node that defines a linear X-Y circle with center (0,0) in X-Y plane.

ClipPlane.title: ClipPlane
ClipPlane.description: ClipPlane specifies a single plane equation used to clip (i.

CollidableOffset.title: CollidableOffset
CollidableOffset.description: CollidableOffset repositions geometry relative to center of owning body.

CollidableShape.title: CollidableShape
CollidableShape.description: CollidableShape connects the collision detection system, the rigid body model, and the renderable scene graph.

Collision.title: Collision
Collision.description: Collision detects camera-to-object contact using current view and NavigationInfo avatarSize.

CollisionCollection.title: CollisionCollection
CollisionCollection.description: CollisionCollection holds a collection of objects that can be managed as a single entity for resolution of inter-object collisions.

CollisionSpace.title: CollisionSpace
CollisionSpace.description: CollisionSpace holds collection of objects considered together for resolution of inter-object collisions.

Color.title: Color
Color.description: Color node defines a set of RGB color values that apply either to a sibling Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, or else to a parent ElevationGrid node.

ColorChaser.title: ColorChaser
ColorChaser.description: ColorChaser generates a series of SFColor values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

ColorDamper.title: ColorDamper
ColorDamper.description: ColorDamper generates a series of RGB color values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

ColorInterpolator.title: ColorInterpolator
ColorInterpolator.description: ColorInterpolator generates a range of color values.

ColorRGBA.title: ColorRGBA
ColorRGBA.description: ColorRGBA node defines a set of RGBA color values that apply either to a sibling Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, or else to a parent ElevationGrid node.

ComposedCubeMapTexture.title: ComposedCubeMapTexture
ComposedCubeMapTexture.description: ComposedCubeMapTexture is a texture node that defines a cubic environment map source as an explicit set of images drawn from individual 2D texture nodes.

ComposedShader.title: ComposedShader
ComposedShader.description: ComposedShader can contain field declarations, but no CDATA section of plain-text source code, since programs are composed from child ShaderPart nodes.

ComposedTexture3D.title: ComposedTexture3D
ComposedTexture3D.description: ComposedTexture3D defines a 3D image-based texture map as a collection of 2D texture sources at various depths.

ComposedVolumeStyle.title: ComposedVolumeStyle
ComposedVolumeStyle.description: ComposedVolumeStyle allows compositing multiple rendering styles into single rendering pass.

ConeEmitter.title: ConeEmitter
ConeEmitter.description: ConeEmitter generates all available particles from a specific point in space.

Contact.title: Contact
Contact.description: Contact nodes are produced as output events when two collidable objects or spaces make contact.

Contour2D.title: Contour2D
Contour2D.description: Contour2D groups a set of curve segments into a composite contour.

ContourPolyline2D.title: ContourPolyline2D
ContourPolyline2D.description: ContourPolyline2D defines a linear curve segment as part of a trimming contour in the u-v domain of a NURBS surface.

Convolver.title: Convolver
Convolver.description: Convolver performs a linear convolution on a given AudioBuffer, often used to achieve a reverberation effect.

Coordinate.title: Coordinate
Coordinate.description: Coordinate builds geometry by defining a set of 3D coordinate (triplet) point values.

CoordinateChaser.title: CoordinateChaser
CoordinateChaser.description: CoordinateChaser generates a series of coordinate arrays that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

CoordinateDamper.title: CoordinateDamper
CoordinateDamper.description: CoordinateDamper generates a series of coordinate arrays that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

CoordinateDouble.title: CoordinateDouble
CoordinateDouble.description: CoordinateDouble builds geometry by defining a set of 3D coordinate (triplet) point values.

CoordinateInterpolator.title: CoordinateInterpolator
CoordinateInterpolator.description: CoordinateInterpolator linearly interpolates among a list of 3-tuple MFVec3f arrays, producing a single MFVec3f array that is fractional average between two nearest arrays in the list.

CoordinateInterpolator2D.title: CoordinateInterpolator2D
CoordinateInterpolator2D.description: CoordinateInterpolator2D generates a series of SFVec2f or MFVec2f 2-tuple float values.

CylinderSensor.title: CylinderSensor
CylinderSensor.description: CylinderSensor converts pointer motion (for example, a mouse or wand) into rotation values using an invisible cylinder aligned with local Y-axis.

Delay.title: Delay
Delay.description: Delay causes a time delay between the arrival of input data and subsequent propagation to the output.

DirectionalLight.title: DirectionalLight
DirectionalLight.description: DirectionalLight might not be scoped by parent Group or Transform at levels 1 or 2.

DISEntityManager.title: DISEntityManager
DISEntityManager.description: DISEntityManager notifies a scene when new DIS ESPDU entities arrive or current entities leave.

DISEntityTypeMapping.title: DISEntityTypeMapping
DISEntityTypeMapping.description: DISEntityTypeMapping provides a best-match mapping from DIS ESPDU entity type information to a specific X3D model, thus providing a visual and behavioral representation that best matches the entity type.

Disk2D.title: Disk2D
Disk2D.description: Disk2D is a geometry node that defines a filled (or partially filled) planar circle with center (0,0).

DoubleAxisHingeJoint.title: DoubleAxisHingeJoint
DoubleAxisHingeJoint.description: DoubleAxisHingeJoint has two independent axes located around a common anchor point.

DynamicsCompressor.title: DynamicsCompressor
DynamicsCompressor.description: DynamicsCompressor node implements a dynamics compression effect, lowering volume of loudest parts of signal and raising volume of softest parts.

EaseInEaseOut.title: EaseInEaseOut
EaseInEaseOut.description: EaseInEaseOut enables gradual animation transitions by modifying TimeSensor fraction outputs.

EdgeEnhancementVolumeStyle.title: EdgeEnhancementVolumeStyle
EdgeEnhancementVolumeStyle.description: EdgeEnhancementVolumeStyle specifies edge enhancement for the volume rendering style.

ElevationGrid.title: ElevationGrid
ElevationGrid.description: ElevationGrid is a geometry node defining a rectangular height field, with default values for a 1m by 1m square at height 0.

EspduTransform.title: EspduTransform
EspduTransform.description: EspduTransform is a networked Transform node that can contain most nodes.

ExplosionEmitter.title: ExplosionEmitter
ExplosionEmitter.description: ExplosionEmitter generates all particles from a specific point in space at the initial time enabled.

Extrusion.title: Extrusion
Extrusion.description: Extrusion is a geometry node that sequentially stretches a 2D cross section along a 3D-spine path in the local coordinate system, creating an outer hull.

FillProperties.title: FillProperties
FillProperties.description: FillProperties indicates whether appearance is filled or hatched for associated geometry nodes inside the same Shape.

FloatVertexAttribute.title: FloatVertexAttribute
FloatVertexAttribute.description: FloatVertexAttribute defines a set of per-vertex single-precision floating-point attributes.

Fog.title: Fog
Fog.description: Fog simulates atmospheric effects by blending distant objects with fog color.

FogCoordinate.title: FogCoordinate
FogCoordinate.description: FogCoordinate defines a set of explicit fog depths on a per-vertex basis, overriding Fog visibilityRange.

FontStyle.title: FontStyle
FontStyle.description: FontStyle is an X3DFontStyleNode that defines the size, family, justification, and other styles used by Text nodes.

ForcePhysicsModel.title: ForcePhysicsModel
ForcePhysicsModel.description: ForcePhysicsModel applies a constant force value to the particles.

Gain.title: Gain
Gain.description: The Gain node amplifies or deamplifies the input signal.

GeneratedCubeMapTexture.title: GeneratedCubeMapTexture
GeneratedCubeMapTexture.description: GeneratedCubeMapTexture is a texture node that defines a cubic environment map that sources its data from internally generated images.

GeoCoordinate.title: GeoCoordinate
GeoCoordinate.description: GeoCoordinate builds geometry as a set of geographic 3D coordinates.

GeoElevationGrid.title: GeoElevationGrid
GeoElevationGrid.description: GeoElevationGrid is a geometry node defining a rectangular height field, with default values for a 1m by 1m square at height 0.

GeoLocation.title: GeoLocation
GeoLocation.description: GeoLocation positions a regular X3D model onto earth's surface.

GeoLOD.title: GeoLOD
GeoLOD.description: Note that MFNode rootNode field can contain multiple nodes and has accessType inputOutput. Meanwhile MFNode children field is outputOnly, unlike other X3DGroupingNode exemplars.

GeoMetadata.title: GeoMetadata
GeoMetadata.description: GeoMetadata includes a generic subset of metadata about the geographic data.

GeoOrigin.title: GeoOrigin
GeoOrigin.description: GeoOrigin is deprecated and discouraged (but nevertheless allowed) in X3D version 3.3. GeoOrigin is restored in X3D version 4.0 for special use on devices with limited floating-point resolution.

GeoPositionInterpolator.title: GeoPositionInterpolator
GeoPositionInterpolator.description: GeoPositionInterpolator animates objects within a geographic coordinate system.

GeoProximitySensor.title: GeoProximitySensor
GeoProximitySensor.description: GeoProximitySensor generates events when the viewer enters, exits and moves within a region of space (defined by a box).

GeoTouchSensor.title: GeoTouchSensor
GeoTouchSensor.description: GeoTouchSensor returns geographic coordinates for the object being selected.

GeoTransform.title: GeoTransform
GeoTransform.description: GeoTransform is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

GeoViewpoint.title: GeoViewpoint
GeoViewpoint.description: GeoViewpoint specifies viewpoints using geographic coordinates.

Group.title: Group
Group.description: Group is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

HAnimDisplacer.title: HAnimDisplacer
HAnimDisplacer.description: HAnimDisplacer nodes alter the shape of coordinate-based geometry within parent HAnimJoint or HAnimSegment nodes.

HAnimHumanoid.title: HAnimHumanoid
HAnimHumanoid.description: The HAnimHumanoid node is used to: (a) store references to the joints, segments, sites, skeleton, optional skin, and fixed viewpoints, (b) serve as a container for the entire humanoid, (c) provide a convenient way of moving the humanoid through its environment, and (d) store human-readable metadata such as name, version, author, copyright, age, gender and other information.

HAnimJoint.title: HAnimJoint
HAnimJoint.description: HAnimJoint node can represent each joint in a body.

HAnimMotion.title: HAnimMotion
HAnimMotion.description: An HAnimMotion node supports discrete frame-by-frame playback for HAnim motion data animation.

HAnimSegment.title: HAnimSegment
HAnimSegment.description: HAnimSegment node contains Shape geometry for each body segment, providing a visual representation of the skeleton segment.

HAnimSite.title: HAnimSite
HAnimSite.description: An HAnimSite node serves three purposes: (a) define an "end effector" location which can be used by an inverse kinematics system, (b) define an attachment point for accessories such as jewelry and clothing, and (c) define a location for a Viewpoint virtual camera in the reference frame of an HAnimSegment (such as a view "through the eyes" of the humanoid for use in multi-user worlds).

ImageCubeMapTexture.title: ImageCubeMapTexture
ImageCubeMapTexture.description: ImageCubeMapTexture is a texture node that defines a cubic environment map source as a single file format that contains multiple images, one for each side.

ImageTexture.title: ImageTexture
ImageTexture.description: ImageTexture maps a 2D-image file onto a geometric shape.

ImageTexture3D.title: ImageTexture3D
ImageTexture3D.description: ImageTexture3D defines a 3D image-based texture map by specifying a single image file that contains complete 3D data.

IndexedFaceSet.title: IndexedFaceSet
IndexedFaceSet.description: IndexedFaceSet defines polygons using index lists corresponding to vertex coordinates.

IndexedLineSet.title: IndexedLineSet
IndexedLineSet.description: IndexedLineSet defines polyline segments using index lists corresponding to vertex coordinates.

IndexedQuadSet.title: IndexedQuadSet
IndexedQuadSet.description: IndexedQuadSet is a geometry node that defines quadrilaterals.

IndexedTriangleFanSet.title: IndexedTriangleFanSet
IndexedTriangleFanSet.description: IndexedTriangleFanSet is a geometry node containing a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, and can also contain Color|ColorRGBA, Normal and TextureCoordinate nodes.

IndexedTriangleSet.title: IndexedTriangleSet
IndexedTriangleSet.description: IndexedTriangleSet is a geometry node containing a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, and can also contain Color|ColorRGBA, Normal and TextureCoordinate nodes.

IndexedTriangleStripSet.title: IndexedTriangleStripSet
IndexedTriangleStripSet.description: IndexedTriangleStripSet is a geometry node containing a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, and can also contain Color|ColorRGBA, Normal and TextureCoordinate nodes.

Inline.title: Inline
Inline.description: Inline can load another X3D or VRML model into the current scene via url.

IntegerSequencer.title: IntegerSequencer
IntegerSequencer.description: IntegerSequencer generates periodic discrete integer values.

IntegerTrigger.title: IntegerTrigger
IntegerTrigger.description: IntegerTrigger converts set_boolean true input events to an integer value (for example, useful when animating whichChoice in a Switch node).

IsoSurfaceVolumeData.title: IsoSurfaceVolumeData
IsoSurfaceVolumeData.description: IsoSurfaceVolumeData displays one or more surfaces extracted from a voxel dataset.

KeySensor.title: KeySensor
KeySensor.description: KeySensor generates events as the user presses keys on the keyboard.

Layer.title: Layer
Layer.description: Layer contains a list of children nodes that define the contents of the layer.

LayerSet.title: LayerSet
LayerSet.description: LayerSet defines a list of layers and a rendering order.

Layout.title: Layout
Layout.description: Layout node is used as layout field of LayoutLayer and LayoutGroup nodes.

LayoutGroup.title: LayoutGroup
LayoutGroup.description: LayoutGroup is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes, whose children are related by a common layout within a parent layout.

LayoutLayer.title: LayoutLayer
LayoutLayer.description: LayoutLayer is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

LinePickSensor.title: LinePickSensor
LinePickSensor.description: LinePickSensor uses one or more pickingGeometry line segments to compute intersections with pickTarget shapes.

LineProperties.title: LineProperties
LineProperties.description: LineProperties allows precise fine-grained control over the rendering style of lines and edges for associated geometry nodes inside the same Shape.

LineSet.title: LineSet
LineSet.description: LineSet is a geometry node that can contain a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node and optionally a Color|ColorRGBA node.

ListenerPointSource.title: ListenerPointSource
ListenerPointSource.description: ListenerPointSource node represents position and orientation of a person listening to virtual sound in the audio scene, and provides single or multiple sound channels as output.

LoadSensor.title: LoadSensor
LoadSensor.description: LoadSensor generates events as watchList child nodes are either loaded or fail to load.

LocalFog.title: LocalFog
LocalFog.description: LocalFog simulates atmospheric effects by blending distant objects with fog color.

LOD.title: LOD
LOD.description: LOD (Level Of Detail) uses camera-to-object distance to switch among contained child levels.

Material.title: Material
Material.description: Material specifies surface rendering properties for associated geometry nodes.

Matrix3VertexAttribute.title: Matrix3VertexAttribute
Matrix3VertexAttribute.description: Matrix3VertexAttribute defines a set of per-vertex 3x3 matrix attributes.

Matrix4VertexAttribute.title: Matrix4VertexAttribute
Matrix4VertexAttribute.description: Matrix4VertexAttribute defines a set of per-vertex 4x4 matrix attributes.

MetadataBoolean.title: MetadataBoolean
MetadataBoolean.description: The metadata provided by this node is contained in the Boolean values of the value field.

MetadataDouble.title: MetadataDouble
MetadataDouble.description: The metadata provided by this node is contained in the double-precision floating point numbers of the value field.

MetadataFloat.title: MetadataFloat
MetadataFloat.description: The metadata provided by this node is contained in the single-precision floating point numbers of the value field.

MetadataInteger.title: MetadataInteger
MetadataInteger.description: The metadata provided by this node is contained in the integer numbers of the value field.

MetadataSet.title: MetadataSet
MetadataSet.description: The metadata provided by this node is contained in the metadata nodes of the value field.

MetadataString.title: MetadataString
MetadataString.description: The metadata provided by this node is contained in the strings of the value field.

MicrophoneSource.title: MicrophoneSource
MicrophoneSource.description: MicrophoneSource captures input from a physical microphone in the real world.

MotorJoint.title: MotorJoint
MotorJoint.description: MotorJoint drives relative angular velocities between body1 and body2 within a common reference frame.

MovieTexture.title: MovieTexture
MovieTexture.description: MovieTexture applies a 2D movie image to surface geometry, or provides audio for a Sound node.

MultiTexture.title: MultiTexture
MultiTexture.description: MultiTexture applies several individual textures to a single geometry node, enabling a variety of visual effects that include light mapping and environment mapping.

MultiTextureCoordinate.title: MultiTextureCoordinate
MultiTextureCoordinate.description: MultiTextureCoordinate contains multiple TextureCoordinate or TextureCoordinateGenerator nodes, for use by a parent polygonal geometry node such as IndexedFaceSet or a Triangle* node.

MultiTextureTransform.title: MultiTextureTransform
MultiTextureTransform.description: MultiTextureTransform contains multiple TextureTransform nodes, each provided for use by corresponding ImageTexture MovieTexture or PixelTexture nodes within a sibling MultiTexture node.

NavigationInfo.title: NavigationInfo
NavigationInfo.description: NavigationInfo describes the user's viewing model, user navigation-interaction modalities, and also dimensional characteristics of the user's (typically invisible) avatar.

Normal.title: Normal
Normal.description: Normal defines a set of 3D surface-normal vectors that apply either to a sibling Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, or else to a parent ElevationGrid node.

NormalInterpolator.title: NormalInterpolator
NormalInterpolator.description: NormalInterpolator generates a series of normal (perpendicular) 3-tuple SFVec3f values.

NurbsCurve.title: NurbsCurve
NurbsCurve.description: NurbsCurve is a 3D curve analogous to NurbsPatchSurface.

NurbsCurve2D.title: NurbsCurve2D
NurbsCurve2D.description: NurbsCurve2D defines a trimming segment that is part of a trimming contour in the u-v domain of a surface.

NurbsOrientationInterpolator.title: NurbsOrientationInterpolator
NurbsOrientationInterpolator.description: NurbsOrientationInterpolator describes a 3D NURBS curve and outputs interpolated orientation values.

NurbsPatchSurface.title: NurbsPatchSurface
NurbsPatchSurface.description: NurbsPatchSurface defines a contiguous 3D Non-Uniform Rational B-Spline (NURBS) surface.

NurbsPositionInterpolator.title: NurbsPositionInterpolator
NurbsPositionInterpolator.description: NurbsPositionInterpolator describes a 3D NURBS curve and outputs interpolated position values.

NurbsSet.title: NurbsSet
NurbsSet.description: NurbsSet collects a set of NurbsSurface nodes into a common group and treats NurbsSurface set as a unit during tessellation, thereby enforcing tessellation continuity along borders.

NurbsSurfaceInterpolator.title: NurbsSurfaceInterpolator
NurbsSurfaceInterpolator.description: NurbsSurfaceInterpolator describes a 3D NURBS curve and outputs interpolated position and normal values.

NurbsSweptSurface.title: NurbsSweptSurface
NurbsSweptSurface.description: NurbsSweptSurface uses a trajectoryCurve path to describe a generalized surface that is swept by a crossSectionCurve.

NurbsSwungSurface.title: NurbsSwungSurface
NurbsSwungSurface.description: NurbsSwungSurface contains a profileCurve and a trajectoryCurve [X3DNurbsControlCurveNode].

NurbsTextureCoordinate.title: NurbsTextureCoordinate
NurbsTextureCoordinate.description: NurbsTextureCoordinate describes a 3D NURBS surface in the parametric domain of its surface host, specifying mapping of texture onto the surface.

NurbsTrimmedSurface.title: NurbsTrimmedSurface
NurbsTrimmedSurface.description: NurbsTrimmedSurface generates texture coordinates from a Non-Uniform Rational B-Spline (NURBS) surface.

OpacityMapVolumeStyle.title: OpacityMapVolumeStyle
OpacityMapVolumeStyle.description: OpacityMapVolumeStyle specifies that volumetric data is rendered using opacity mapped to a transfer function texture.

OrientationChaser.title: OrientationChaser
OrientationChaser.description: OrientationChaser generates a series of 4-tuple axis-angle SFRotation values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

OrientationDamper.title: OrientationDamper
OrientationDamper.description: OrientationDamper generates a series of 4-tuple axis-angle SFRotation values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

OrientationInterpolator.title: OrientationInterpolator
OrientationInterpolator.description: OrientationInterpolator generates a series of 4-tuple axis-angle SFRotation values.

OrthoViewpoint.title: OrthoViewpoint
OrthoViewpoint.description: OrthoViewpoint provides an orthographic perspective-free view of a scene from a specific location and direction.

OscillatorSource.title: OscillatorSource
OscillatorSource.description: OscillatorSource node represents an audio source generating a periodic waveform, providing a constant tone.

PackagedShader.title: PackagedShader
PackagedShader.description: PackagedShader can contain field declarations, but no CDATA section of plain-text source code.

ParticleSystem.title: ParticleSystem
ParticleSystem.description: ParticleSystem specifies a complete particle system.

PeriodicWave.title: PeriodicWave
PeriodicWave.description: PeriodicWave defines a periodic waveform that can be used to shape the output of an Oscillator.

PhysicalMaterial.title: PhysicalMaterial
PhysicalMaterial.description: PhysicalMaterial specifies surface rendering properties for associated geometry nodes.

PickableGroup.title: PickableGroup
PickableGroup.description: PickableGroup is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

PixelTexture.title: PixelTexture
PixelTexture.description: PixelTexture creates a 2D-image texture map using a numeric array of pixel values.

PixelTexture3D.title: PixelTexture3D
PixelTexture3D.description: PixelTexture3D defines a 3D image-based texture map as an explicit array of pixel values (image field).

PlaneSensor.title: PlaneSensor
PlaneSensor.description: PlaneSensor converts pointing device motion into 2D translation parallel to the local Z=0 plane.

PointEmitter.title: PointEmitter
PointEmitter.description: PointEmitter generates particles from a specific point in space using the specified direction and speed.

PointLight.title: PointLight
PointLight.description: Linear attenuation may occur at level 2, full support at level 3.

PointPickSensor.title: PointPickSensor
PointPickSensor.description: PointPickSensor tests one or more pickingGeometry points in space as lying inside the provided pickTarget geometry.

PointProperties.title: PointProperties
PointProperties.description: PointProperties allows precise fine-grained control over the rendering style of PointSet node points inside the same Shape.

PointSet.title: PointSet
PointSet.description: PointSet is a node that contains a set of colored 3D points, represented by contained Color|ColorRGBA and Coordinate|CoordinateDouble nodes.

Polyline2D.title: Polyline2D
Polyline2D.description: Polyline2D is a geometry node that defines a connected set of vertices in a contiguous set of line segments in X-Y plane.

PolylineEmitter.title: PolylineEmitter
PolylineEmitter.description: PolylineEmitter emits particles along a single polyline.

Polypoint2D.title: Polypoint2D
Polypoint2D.description: Polypoint2D is a geometry node that defines a set of 2D points in X-Y plane.

PositionChaser.title: PositionChaser
PositionChaser.description: PositionChaser generates a series of position values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

PositionChaser2D.title: PositionChaser2D
PositionChaser2D.description: PositionChaser2D generates a series of 2D position values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

PositionDamper.title: PositionDamper
PositionDamper.description: PositionDamper generates a series of position values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

PositionDamper2D.title: PositionDamper2D
PositionDamper2D.description: PositionDamper2D generates a series of 2D floating-point values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

PositionInterpolator.title: PositionInterpolator
PositionInterpolator.description: PositionInterpolator generates a series of 3-tuple SFVec3f values.

PositionInterpolator2D.title: PositionInterpolator2D
PositionInterpolator2D.description: PositionInterpolator2D generates a series of SFVec2f values.

PrimitivePickSensor.title: PrimitivePickSensor
PrimitivePickSensor.description: If a non-uniform scale is applied to the pick sensor, correct results may require level 3 support.

ProgramShader.title: ProgramShader
ProgramShader.description: ProgramShader contains no field declarations and no plain-text source code.

ProjectionVolumeStyle.title: ProjectionVolumeStyle
ProjectionVolumeStyle.description: ProjectionVolumeStyle uses voxel data to directly generate output color.

ProtoInstance.title: ProtoInstance
ProtoInstance.description: ProtoInstance can override field default values via fieldValue initializations. Non-recursive nested ProtoInstance and ProtoDeclare statements are allowed within a ProtoDeclare.

ProximitySensor.title: ProximitySensor
ProximitySensor.description: ProximitySensor generates events when the viewer enters, exits and moves within a region of space (defined by a box).

QuadSet.title: QuadSet
QuadSet.description: QuadSet is a geometry node that defines quadrilaterals.

ReceiverPdu.title: ReceiverPdu
ReceiverPdu.description: ReceiverPdu is a networked Protocol Data Unit (PDU) information node that transmits the state of radio frequency (RF) receivers modeled in a simulation.

Rectangle2D.title: Rectangle2D
Rectangle2D.description: Rectangle2D is a geometry node that defines a 2D rectangle in X-Y plane.

RigidBody.title: RigidBody
RigidBody.description: RigidBody describes a collection of shapes with a mass distribution that is affected by the physics model.

RigidBodyCollection.title: RigidBodyCollection
RigidBodyCollection.description: RigidBodyCollection represents a system of bodies that interact within a single physics model.

ScalarChaser.title: ScalarChaser
ScalarChaser.description: ScalarChaser generates a series of single floating-point values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

ScalarDamper.title: ScalarDamper
ScalarDamper.description: ScalarDamper generates a series of floating-point values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

ScreenFontStyle.title: ScreenFontStyle
ScreenFontStyle.description: ScreenFontStyle is an X3DFontStyleNode defines the size, family, justification, and other styles used within a screen layout.

ScreenGroup.title: ScreenGroup
ScreenGroup.description: ScreenGroup is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

Script.title: Script
Script.description: Script contains author-programmed event behaviors for a scene.

SegmentedVolumeData.title: SegmentedVolumeData
SegmentedVolumeData.description: SegmentedVolumeData displays a segmented voxel dataset with different RenderStyle nodes.

ShadedVolumeStyle.title: ShadedVolumeStyle
ShadedVolumeStyle.description: All fields fully supported except shadows supported with at least Phong shading at level 3. All fields fully supported with at least Phong shading and Henyey-Greenstein phase function, shadows fully supported at level 4.

ShaderPart.title: ShaderPart
ShaderPart.description: ShaderPart can contain a CDATA section of plain-text source code.

ShaderProgram.title: ShaderProgram
ShaderProgram.description: ShaderProgram can contain field declarations and a CDATA section of plain-text source code.

Shape.title: Shape
Shape.description: Shape can appear under any grouping node.

SignalPdu.title: SignalPdu
SignalPdu.description: SignalPdu is a networked Protocol Data Unit (PDU) information node that communicates the transmission of voice, audio or other data modeled in a simulation.

SilhouetteEnhancementVolumeStyle.title: SilhouetteEnhancementVolumeStyle
SilhouetteEnhancementVolumeStyle.description: SilhouetteEnhancementVolumeStyle specifies that volumetric data is rendered with silhouette enhancement.

SingleAxisHingeJoint.title: SingleAxisHingeJoint
SingleAxisHingeJoint.description: SingleAxisHingeJoint has single axis about which to rotate, similar to a traditional door hinge. Contains two RigidBody nodes (containerField values body1, body2).

SliderJoint.title: SliderJoint
SliderJoint.description: SliderJoint constrains all movement between body1 and body2 along a single axis. Contains two RigidBody nodes (containerField values body1, body2).

Sound.title: Sound
Sound.description: The Sound node controls the 3D spatialization of sound playback by a child AudioClip or MovieTexture node.

SpatialSound.title: SpatialSound
SpatialSound.description: The SpatialSound node controls the 3D spatialization of sound playback by a child AudioClip or MovieTexture node.

Sphere.title: Sphere
Sphere.description: Sphere is a geometry node, representing a perfectly round geometrical object that is the surface of a completely round ball.

SphereSensor.title: SphereSensor
SphereSensor.description: SphereSensor converts pointing device motion into a spherical rotation about the origin of the local coordinate system.

SplinePositionInterpolator.title: SplinePositionInterpolator
SplinePositionInterpolator.description: SplinePositionInterpolator performs non-linear interpolation among paired lists of 3-tuple values and velocities to produce an SFVec3f value_changed output event.

SplinePositionInterpolator2D.title: SplinePositionInterpolator2D
SplinePositionInterpolator2D.description: SplinePositionInterpolator2D performs non-linear interpolation among paired lists of 2-tuple values and velocities to produce an SFVec2f value_changed output event.

SplineScalarInterpolator.title: SplineScalarInterpolator
SplineScalarInterpolator.description: SplineScalarInterpolator performs non-linear interpolation among paired lists of float values and velocities to produce an SFFloat value_changed output event.

SpotLight.title: SpotLight
SpotLight.description: Linear attenuation may occur at level 2, full support at level 3.

SquadOrientationInterpolator.title: SquadOrientationInterpolator
SquadOrientationInterpolator.description: SquadOrientationInterpolator performs non-linear interpolation among paired lists of rotation values to produce an SFRotation value_changed output event.

StaticGroup.title: StaticGroup
StaticGroup.description: StaticGroup is similar to Group node but does not allow access to children after creation time.

StreamAudioDestination.title: StreamAudioDestination
StreamAudioDestination.description: StreamAudioDestination node represents the final audio destination via a media stream.

StreamAudioSource.title: StreamAudioSource
StreamAudioSource.description: StreamAudioSource operates as an audio source whose media is received from a MediaStream obtained using the WebRTC or Media Capture and Streams APIs.

StringSensor.title: StringSensor
StringSensor.description: StringSensor generates events as the user presses keys on the keyboard.

SurfaceEmitter.title: SurfaceEmitter
SurfaceEmitter.description: SurfaceEmitter generates particles from the surface of an object.

Switch.title: Switch
Switch.description: Switch is a Grouping node that only renders one (or zero) child at a time.

TexCoordChaser2D.title: TexCoordChaser2D
TexCoordChaser2D.description: TexCoordChaser2D generates a series of single floating-point values that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

TexCoordDamper2D.title: TexCoordDamper2D
TexCoordDamper2D.description: TexCoordDamper2D generates a series of 2D floating-point arrays that progressively change from initial value to destination value.

Text.title: Text
Text.description: Text is a 2D (flat) geometry node that can contain multiple lines of string values.

TextureBackground.title: TextureBackground
TextureBackground.description: TextureBackground simulates ground and sky, using vertical arrays of wraparound color values, TextureBackground can also provide backdrop texture images on all six sides.

TextureCoordinate.title: TextureCoordinate
TextureCoordinate.description: TextureCoordinate specifies 2D (s,t) texture-coordinate points, used by vertex-based geometry nodes (such as IndexedFaceSet or ElevationGrid) to map textures to vertices (and patches to NURBS surfaces).

TextureCoordinate3D.title: TextureCoordinate3D
TextureCoordinate3D.description: TextureCoordinate3D specifies a set of 3D texture coordinates used by vertex-based geometry nodes (such as IndexedFaceSet or ElevationGrid) to map 3D textures to vertices.

TextureCoordinate4D.title: TextureCoordinate4D
TextureCoordinate4D.description: TextureCoordinate4D specifies a set of 4D (homogeneous 3D) texture coordinates used by vertex-based geometry nodes (such as IndexedFaceSet or ElevationGrid) to map 3D textures to vertices.

TextureCoordinateGenerator.title: TextureCoordinateGenerator
TextureCoordinateGenerator.description: TextureCoordinateGenerator computes 2D (s,t) texture-coordinate points, used by vertex-based geometry nodes (such as IndexedFaceSet or ElevationGrid) to map textures to vertices (and patches to NURBS surfaces).

TextureProjector.title: TextureProjector
TextureProjector.description: TextureProjector is similar to a light that projects a texture into the scene, illuminating geometry that intersects the perspective projection volume.

TextureProjectorParallel.title: TextureProjectorParallel
TextureProjectorParallel.description: TextureProjectorParallel is similar to a light that projects a texture into the scene, illuminating geometry that intersects the parallel projection volume.

TextureProperties.title: TextureProperties
TextureProperties.description: TextureProperties allows precise fine-grained control over application of image textures to geometry.

TextureTransform.title: TextureTransform
TextureTransform.description: TextureTransform shifts 2D texture coordinates for positioning, orienting and scaling image textures on geometry.

TextureTransform3D.title: TextureTransform3D
TextureTransform3D.description: TextureTransform3D applies a 3D transformation to texture coordinates.

TextureTransformMatrix3D.title: TextureTransformMatrix3D
TextureTransformMatrix3D.description: TextureTransformMatrix3D applies a 3D transformation to texture coordinates.

TimeSensor.title: TimeSensor
TimeSensor.description: TimeSensor continuously generates events as time passes.

TimeTrigger.title: TimeTrigger
TimeTrigger.description: TimeTrigger converts boolean true events to time events.

ToneMappedVolumeStyle.title: ToneMappedVolumeStyle
ToneMappedVolumeStyle.description: ToneMappedVolumeStyle specifies that volumetric data is rendered with Gooch shading model of two-toned warm/cool coloring.

TouchSensor.title: TouchSensor
TouchSensor.description: TouchSensor tracks location and state of the pointing device, detecting when a user points at or selects (activates) geometry.

Transform.title: Transform
Transform.description: Transform is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

TransformSensor.title: TransformSensor
TransformSensor.description: TransformSensor generates output events when its targetObject enters, exits, and moves within a region in space (defined by a box).

TransmitterPdu.title: TransmitterPdu
TransmitterPdu.description: TransmitterPdu is a networked Protocol Data Unit (PDU) information node that provides detailed information about a radio transmitter modeled in a simulation.

TriangleFanSet.title: TriangleFanSet
TriangleFanSet.description: TriangleFanSet is a geometry node containing a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, and can also contain Color|ColorRGBA, Normal and TextureCoordinate nodes.

TriangleSet.title: TriangleSet
TriangleSet.description: TriangleSet is a geometry node containing a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, and can also contain Color|ColorRGBA, Normal and TextureCoordinate nodes.

TriangleSet2D.title: TriangleSet2D
TriangleSet2D.description: TriangleSet2D is a geometry node that defines a set of filled 2D triangles in X-Y plane.

TriangleStripSet.title: TriangleStripSet
TriangleStripSet.description: TriangleStripSet is a geometry node containing a Coordinate|CoordinateDouble node, and can also contain Color|ColorRGBA, Normal and TextureCoordinate nodes.

TwoSidedMaterial.title: TwoSidedMaterial
TwoSidedMaterial.description: TwoSidedMaterial specifies surface rendering properties for associated geometry nodes, for outer (front) and inner (back) sides of polygons.

UniversalJoint.title: UniversalJoint
UniversalJoint.description: UniversalJoint is like a BallJoint that constrains an extra degree of rotational freedom.

UnlitMaterial.title: UnlitMaterial
UnlitMaterial.description: UnlitMaterial specifies surface rendering properties for associated geometry nodes.

Viewpoint.title: Viewpoint
Viewpoint.description: Viewpoint provides a specific location and direction where the user may view the scene.

ViewpointGroup.title: ViewpointGroup
ViewpointGroup.description: ViewpointGroup can contain Viewpoint, OrthoViewpoint, GeoViewpoint and other ViewpointGroup nodes for better user-navigation support with a shared description on the viewpoint list.

Viewport.title: Viewport
Viewport.description: Viewport is a Grouping node that can contain most nodes.

VisibilitySensor.title: VisibilitySensor
VisibilitySensor.description: VisibilitySensor detects when user can see a specific object or region as they navigate the world.

VolumeData.title: VolumeData
VolumeData.description: VolumeData displays a simple non-segmented voxel dataset with a single RenderStyle node.

VolumeEmitter.title: VolumeEmitter
VolumeEmitter.description: VolumeEmitter emits particles from a random position confined within the given closed geometry volume.

VolumePickSensor.title: VolumePickSensor
VolumePickSensor.description: VolumePickSensor tests picking intersections using the pickingGeometry against the pickTarget geometry volume.

WaveShaper.title: WaveShaper
WaveShaper.description: WaveShaper node represents a nonlinear distorter that applies a wave-shaping distortion curve to the signal.

WindPhysicsModel.title: WindPhysicsModel
WindPhysicsModel.description: WindPhysicsModel applies a wind effect to the particles.

WorldInfo.title: WorldInfo
WorldInfo.description: WorldInfo contains a title and simple persistent metadata information about an X3D scene. This node is strictly for documentation purposes and has no effect on the visual appearance or behaviour of the world.

EnvironmentLight.title: EnvironmentLight
EnvironmentLight.description: EnvironmentLight ... This node only affects the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes.

ImageTextureAtlas.title: ImageTextureAtlas
ImageTextureAtlas.description: ImageTextureAtlas defines a 3D image-based texture map by specifying a single image file that contains slices for complete 3D data.

AnisotropyMaterialExtension.title: AnisotropyMaterialExtension
AnisotropyMaterialExtension.description: AnisotropyMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

BlendMode.title: BlendMode
BlendMode.description: BlendMode controls how pixels of an objects are drawn. Pixels can be drawn using a function that blends the incoming (source) RGBA values with the RGBA values that are already in the frame buffer (the destination values). BlendMode is an X3DAppearanceChildNode node that handles blend operations.

ClearcoatMaterialExtension.title: ClearcoatMaterialExtension
ClearcoatMaterialExtension.description: ClearcoatMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

DepthMode.title: DepthMode
DepthMode.description: DepthMode contains parameters that are specific for depth control, like the value used for depth buffer comparisons.

DispersionMaterialExtension.title: DispersionMaterialExtension
DispersionMaterialExtension.description: DispersionMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

EmissiveStrengthMaterialExtension.title: EmissiveStrengthMaterialExtension
EmissiveStrengthMaterialExtension.description: EmissiveStrengthMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes.

IORMaterialExtension.title: IORMaterialExtension
IORMaterialExtension.description: IORMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

InstancedShape.title: InstancedShape
InstancedShape.description: InstancedShape can appear under any grouping node. InstancedShape can contain an Appearance node and a geometry node (for example one of the primitives Box Cone Cylinder Sphere Text, one of ElevationGrid Extrusion IndexedFaceSet IndexedLineSet LineSet PointSet, or one of the other geometry nodes) and this geometry node is instantiated as often as transformations are provided.

IridescenceMaterialExtension.title: IridescenceMaterialExtension
IridescenceMaterialExtension.description: IridescenceMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

SheenMaterialExtension.title: SheenMaterialExtension
SheenMaterialExtension.description: SheenMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

SpecularGlossinessMaterial.title: SpecularGlossinessMaterial
SpecularGlossinessMaterial.description: SpecularGlossinessMaterial specifies surface rendering properties for associated geometry nodes. Material attributes are used by the X3D lighting equations during rendering.

SpecularMaterialExtension.title: SpecularMaterialExtension
SpecularMaterialExtension.description: SpecularMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

TransmissionMaterialExtension.title: TransmissionMaterialExtension
TransmissionMaterialExtension.description: TransmissionMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

VolumeMaterialExtension.title: VolumeMaterialExtension
VolumeMaterialExtension.description: VolumeMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

DiffuseTransmissionMaterialExtension.title: DiffuseTransmissionMaterialExtension
DiffuseTransmissionMaterialExtension.description: DiffuseTransmissionMaterialExtension is an extension for the PhysicalMaterial and SpecularGlossinessMaterial nodes. For this node to have an effect, add an EnvironmentLight node.

component.title: component
component.description: Functional summary: each added component statement indicates needed scene functionality support above the given X3D profile.

connect.title: connect
connect.description: Functional summary: connect statements define event-routing connections between node fields defined inside a ProtoBody declaration back to corresponding ProtoInterface fields.

EXPORT.title: EXPORT
EXPORT.description: Functional summary: EXPORT exposes a local node for ROUTE passing of event values when the current Scene is included via Inline by a parent external world. These connections allow event values to be exchanged via ROUTE statements between a parent model and a child Inline model.

ExternProtoDeclare.title: ExternProtoDeclare
ExternProtoDeclare.description: ExternProtoDeclare refers to a ProtoDeclare node declaration provided in another file. ExternProtoDeclare interfaces are defined by field statements (and without IS/connect statements).

field.title: field
field.description: Functional summary: a field statement defines an interface attribute or node. Each field statement can contain either attribute-value or node content.

fieldValue.title: fieldValue
fieldValue.description: Functional summary: a fieldValue statement re-initializes the default value of a field in a ProtoInstance. Each fieldValue statement can contain either attribute-value or node content.

head.title: head
head.description: Functional summary: each X3D scene includes a head statement that can contain component, unit and meta statements.

IMPORT.title: IMPORT
IMPORT.description: Functional summary: IMPORT provides ROUTE access to a node that has a corresponding EXPORT statement within an Inline scene. These connections allow event values to be exchanged via ROUTE statements between a parent model and a child Inline model.

IS.title: IS
IS.description: Functional summary: the IS statement connects node fields defined inside a ProtoBody declaration back to corresponding ProtoInterface fields. IS/connect statements can be added if the parent node is within a ProtoBody and connect statements define correspondences between prototype fields and built-in node fields.

meta.title: meta
meta.description: Functional summary: the meta statement provides metadata information about a scene, where name and content attributes provide attribute=value metadata pairs.

ProtoBody.title: ProtoBody
ProtoBody.description: ProtoBody contains the definition nodes for new Prototype nodes.

ProtoDeclare.title: ProtoDeclare
ProtoDeclare.description: ProtoDeclare defines new Prototype nodes. Nested ProtoDeclares and ProtoInstances are allowed by the specification.

ProtoInterface.title: ProtoInterface
ProtoInterface.description: ProtoInterface defines fields for new Prototype nodes.

ROUTE.title: ROUTE
ROUTE.description: ROUTE connects output fields of event-producing nodes to input fields of event-consuming nodes.

Scene.title: Scene
Scene.description: Scene is the implicit root node of the X3D scene graph.

unit.title: unit
unit.description: Functional summary: unit statement defines data-conversion factors for typed values defined in a scene.

X3D.title: X3D
X3D.description: X3D is the root node for an Extensible 3D (X3D) Graphics model.
